# Pi Capture System — Setup Guide

## Files
| File             | Runs on  | Purpose                        |
|------------------|----------|-------------------------------|
| `slave_server.py`| Slave Pi | Flask REST API + camera        |
| `master_app.py`  | Master Pi| Tkinter GUI control app        |
| `requirements_slave.txt` | Slave Pi | Python deps          |
| `requirements_master.txt`| Master Pi| Python deps          |

---

## 1  Find your Slave Pi's IP address
On the Slave Pi run:
```bash
hostname -I
```
Note the IP (e.g. `192.168.1.100`). You'll type this into the master GUI.

---

## 2  Slave Pi setup

### Install system packages
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y python3-pip python3-flask libcamera-tools
```

### Install Python packages
```bash
pip3 install flask --break-system-packages
```

### (Recommended) Install picamera2 if using Pi Camera Module
```bash
sudo apt install -y python3-picamera2
```

### Copy `slave_server.py` to the Slave Pi, then run it
```bash
python3 slave_server.py
```

### (Optional) Auto-start on boot with systemd
```ini
# /etc/systemd/system/pi-capture-slave.service
[Unit]
Description=Pi Capture Slave Server
After=network.target

[Service]
ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3 /home/pi/slave_server.py
WorkingDirectory=/home/pi
Restart=always
User=pi

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```
```bash
sudo systemctl enable pi-capture-slave
sudo systemctl start pi-capture-slave
```

---

## 3  Master Pi setup

### Install system packages
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y python3-pip python3-tk python3-pil python3-pil.imagetk
```

### Install Python packages
```bash
pip3 install requests pillow --break-system-packages
```

### Copy `master_app.py` to the Master Pi, then run it
```bash
python3 master_app.py
```

---

## 4  Using the GUI

1. Enter the **Slave IP address** in the sidebar (e.g. `192.168.1.100`)
2. Click **Ping Slave** — the dot should turn green (● online)
3. Click **📷 Capture Image** — the image appears on the right panel
4. Click **💾 Save Image** to keep a local copy in `~/Pictures/captures/`

The slave's temporary file is deleted automatically after every capture.

---

## 5  Firewall — open port 5000 on the Slave Pi
```bash
sudo ufw allow 5000/tcp
```

---

## 6  Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| "Cannot reach" | Check both Pis are on same network; verify slave server is running |
| "picamera2 not found" | `sudo apt install python3-picamera2` on the Slave Pi |
| libcamera-still fails | Enable camera in `sudo raspi-config` → Interface Options |
| USB webcam not found | Install `fswebcam`: `sudo apt install fswebcam` |
| Permission denied on camera | Add user to `video` group: `sudo usermod -aG video pi` |